cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.CL

This paper discusses the effectiveness of Open Access mandates and analyzes data related to OA repositories and publication years. The most relevant sub-category for this paper is likely cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as it deals with the management and dissemination of digital content, including OA repositories. The paper also touches on information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) in relation to OA mandates. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) due to its analysis of specific conditions that contribute to mandate effectiveness.
